            . The prisoner was my <rs id="t18340515-62-deflabel352" type="occupation">errand-boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340515-62-defend655 t18340515-62-deflabel352"></join>. On the 21st of April, about half-past nine o'clock in the evening, I received information, and looked into his box - I found two pair of women's boots in it - I got an officer, and gave him into custody - my mother is in partnership with me.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183405150043"></xptr>(The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that he had taken the boots to raise the means of paying for some glass which he had broken, and which his scanty wages could not allow.)</p>
               <p>MR. SAUNDBY. I have been as liberal to him as if he were a child of my own - I never made him pay for any thing - I have threatened him for his carelessness - two odd shoes were found at his mother's lodging.</p>
